  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2009-10-08",
    "date": "2009-11-04T19:50:14Z",
    "text": "Helping Invigorate and Revive our Economy Act of 2009 or the HIRE America Act - Amends Internal Revenue Code provisions relating to the work opportunity tax credit to: (1) increase the rate of such credit to 50% for members of a targeted group and allow a credit for 30% of wages paid to individuals who are not members of a targeted group; (2) increase the rate of such credit for part-time workers; (3) increase the dollar limitation on the wages eligible for such credit for disabled veterans and summer youth employees; and (4) make such credit permanent.\n\nIncreases the rate of the tax credit for employer-provided child care."
  },
